WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.001 --> 00:00:08.122
'Famous child artist Daisy Irani.'

00:00:08.202 --> 00:00:12.108
'She had created great records
in her childhood.'

00:00:12.188 --> 00:00:14.649
'She was born in 1952.'

00:00:14.729 --> 00:00:18.568
"I am short tempered.
I would do something untoward."

00:00:18.648 --> 00:00:22.202
"Do not hit me."

00:00:22.282 --> 00:00:26.851
'Her parents had five children.
She was the fourth child.'

00:00:26.931 --> 00:00:29.959
'Her father had
an Irani restaurant..'

00:00:30.039 --> 00:00:32.377
'..at Mumbai's Grant Road station.'

00:00:32.457 --> 00:00:35.431
'That restaurant was quite famous.'

00:00:35.511 --> 00:00:40.283
'She was about 2.5 years old when
she got a chance to work in a film.'

00:00:40.363 --> 00:00:45.052
'Director Bipin Gupta
was looking for a child artist.'

00:00:45.132 --> 00:00:46.863
'He was looking for a boy.'

00:00:46.943 --> 00:00:52.701
'Daisy Irani was playing in her building
compound wearing her brother's shirt.' 

00:00:52.781 --> 00:00:56.390
'Bipin Gupta thought it was a boy.'

00:00:56.470 --> 00:00:58.512
'So, he met her mother.'

00:00:58.592 --> 00:01:00.485
'Her father didn't want her
to work in films.'

00:01:00.565 --> 00:01:05.526
'But her mother told him she should
be allowed to work in films.'

00:01:05.606 --> 00:01:08.647
'That's how Daisy Irani's
film career began.'

00:01:08.727 --> 00:01:12.088
'There were 10 birds on a tree.' 

00:01:12.714 --> 00:01:17.106
'A hunter shot down a bird.'

00:01:17.605 --> 00:01:22.591
'How many birds
are left on the tree?'

00:01:22.671 --> 00:01:24.523
'None.
- Why not?'

00:01:24.603 --> 00:01:28.118
'Simple. The pigeons flew away
upon hearing the gun shot.'

00:01:28.198 --> 00:01:30.685
'Her first film was 'Taxal'.'

00:01:30.765 --> 00:01:34.626
'After that, famous directors like 
Satyen Bose and B. R. Chopra..

00:01:34.706 --> 00:01:36.672
..came to sign her.' 

00:01:36.752 --> 00:01:39.753
'For a long time,
she played a boy in films.'

00:01:39.833 --> 00:01:43.024
'As she had played a boy
in her first film.'

00:01:43.104 --> 00:01:46.267
'So, everyone offered her
similar roles.'

00:01:46.347 --> 00:01:50.146
'Mom, I want these flowers.
Mom!'

00:01:50.226 --> 00:01:55.308
'Raja, those flowers aren't good.
I'll give you a bouquet.'

00:01:55.388 --> 00:01:59.078
'She was always told
not to look at the camera.'

00:01:59.158 --> 00:02:03.794
'Or touch her face
after the makeup was done.'

00:02:03.874 --> 00:02:06.145
'That's what
she had said to a star.'

00:02:06.225 --> 00:02:09.227
'She had said that to Ashok Kumar.'

00:02:09.307 --> 00:02:12.592
'He got on the sets
and little Daisy told him..'

00:02:12.672 --> 00:02:15.966
'..not to look into the 
camera or touch his face.'

00:02:16.046 --> 00:02:17.186
'There was makeup on his face.' 

00:02:17.266 --> 00:02:19.875
'All those who listened
laughed out loud.'

00:02:23.118 --> 00:02:27.848
'She started to get more work.
She used to work three shifts.'

00:02:27.928 --> 00:02:31.700
'There was so much work,
she couldn't focus on studies.'

00:02:31.780 --> 00:02:33.849
'She had lost her childhood.'

00:02:33.929 --> 00:02:36.038
'Daisy Irani has always said..'

00:02:36.118 --> 00:02:40.065
'..that her sister Honey Irani and she
spent their childhood on the film sets.' 

00:02:40.145 --> 00:02:43.159
'They couldn't do things
that normal children would do.'

00:02:43.239 --> 00:02:45.294
'This is All India Radio.'

00:02:45.374 --> 00:02:50.307
'Master Mitthoo will present
some acts to you.'

00:02:50.387 --> 00:02:53.063
'She had a good rapport
with Meena Kumari.'

00:02:53.143 --> 00:02:57.698
'Meena Kumari loved her
like a mother.'

00:02:57.778 --> 00:03:00.468
'The first film she did with
Meena Kumari was 'Bandish'.'

00:03:00.548 --> 00:03:06.684
'Next, in the film 'Ek Hi Rasta',
Daisy Irani played Meena Kumari's son.' 

00:03:06.764 --> 00:03:09.372
'Moreover, Daisy Irani had acted in..

00:03:09.452 --> 00:03:12.224
..Meena Kumari's last film 
'Gomti Ke Kinare'.

00:03:12.304 --> 00:03:15.183
'Take your toys. Let's play.'

00:03:15.263 --> 00:03:17.494
'No, I don't want the toys.'

00:03:17.574 --> 00:03:21.413
"Let go of your anger."

00:03:21.493 --> 00:03:25.264
"Forget that I scolded you.
Don't be angry with your mother."

00:03:25.344 --> 00:03:29.047
"You are my son. I am your mother.
Give me a smile, dear."

00:03:29.213 --> 00:03:33.467
'Daisy Irani was happy
and had lots of money.'

00:03:33.547 --> 00:03:35.683
'But she also
got slapped and wounded.'

00:03:35.763 --> 00:03:39.317
'Oftentimes, she wasn't
in the mood to cry.'

00:03:39.397 --> 00:03:42.452
'But the scene demanded
that she cry.'

00:03:42.532 --> 00:03:44.669
'Daisy Irani couldn't cry.'

00:03:44.749 --> 00:03:49.507
'Someone would slap her
and she would cry.'

00:03:50.007 --> 00:03:51.710
'Give it to me too.
- Sure.'

00:03:51.790 --> 00:03:53.439
'Go away, you idiot!'

00:03:53.519 --> 00:03:56.494
'The film 'Hum Panchhi Ek Daal Ke'
was the most hit film.'

00:03:56.574 --> 00:04:01.124
'Daisy Irani had Jagdeep and
Mohan Choti as co-stars.'

00:04:01.204 --> 00:04:04.709
'The film bagged the National Award
and she got an invite from Delhi.'

00:04:04.789 --> 00:04:06.560
'All the actors went to Delhi.'

00:04:06.640 --> 00:04:11.033
'They met India's first Prime Minister
Pandit Jawaharlal Nehru.'

00:04:11.113 --> 00:04:15.750
'The children were happy at the function.
As they left, Daisy's mother told her..' 

00:04:15.830 --> 00:04:20.291
'..to thank Uncle Nehru
for the efforts.'

00:04:20.371 --> 00:04:23.547
'But Daisy Irani told Nehru,
'Sorry for the trouble.''

00:04:23.627 --> 00:04:25.939
'Uncle Nehru was shocked
to hear it.'

00:04:26.019 --> 00:04:29.992
'Pandit Nehru called Daisy's mother
and asked if Daisy attended school.'

00:04:30.072 --> 00:04:31.552
'Her mother told him she didn't.'

00:04:31.632 --> 00:04:36.384
'Uncle Nehru wrote a letter that the 
girl must get admission in a school.' 

00:04:36.601 --> 00:04:39.736
'Finally, she got admission
in a school.'

00:04:39.816 --> 00:04:44.413
'She was nine years old
and got admitted to Class 4.'

00:04:44.493 --> 00:04:46.736
'She was in Class 4
for three years.'

00:04:46.816 --> 00:04:48.817
'Gradually, she gave up studies.'

00:04:48.897 --> 00:04:51.182
'But her brothers
helped her a lot.'

00:04:51.262 --> 00:04:55.804
'They gave her comic books through
which she learned to speak English.' 

00:04:56.006 --> 00:04:58.898
'Read this book.
- Very well.'

00:04:58.978 --> 00:05:02.871
'Childhood passed by
and she grew up.'

00:05:03.095 --> 00:05:07.033
'She got very little work
and she wondered why.'

00:05:07.113 --> 00:05:09.735
'During that time, 
her mother launched a film..

00:05:09.815 --> 00:05:11.344
..with her elder daughter
 in the lead.' 

00:05:11.424 --> 00:05:13.506
'The hero was Salim Khan.'

00:05:13.586 --> 00:05:17.257
'The father of superstar
Salman Khan.'

00:05:17.337 --> 00:05:20.330
'The film didn't do well and her 
family got into financial problems.' 

00:05:20.410 --> 00:05:22.654
'Gradually, they got bankrupt.'

00:05:22.734 --> 00:05:27.127
'Let nobody else meet your fate.'

00:05:27.207 --> 00:05:32.411
'Daisy Irani used to say that
her mother spent all her money.'

00:05:32.491 --> 00:05:34.869
'But she wasn't angry about it.'

00:05:34.949 --> 00:05:37.518
'Her father didn't take
a penny from her.'

00:05:37.598 --> 00:05:39.450
'His restaurant
continued to do well.'

00:05:39.530 --> 00:05:43.234
'He had rightly said that
his wife was very beautiful.'

00:05:43.314 --> 00:05:46.598
'Now, let's turn to Daisy Irani's
personal life.'

00:05:46.678 --> 00:05:51.039
'She had to dance in a film.
The director was K. K. Shukla.'

00:05:51.119 --> 00:05:54.990
'She met him and
fell in love with him.'

00:05:55.070 --> 00:05:56.895
'Soon, they got married.'

00:05:56.975 --> 00:05:59.233
'Post marriage,
she became a housewife.'

00:05:59.313 --> 00:06:01.665
'They had three kids.'

00:06:01.745 --> 00:06:05.017
'Later, she opened her acting class.'

00:06:05.638 --> 00:06:10.165
'If you don't listen to me,
you'll have to leave this house.'

00:06:10.245 --> 00:06:13.178
'Daisy Irani has watched
very few of her films.'

00:06:13.258 --> 00:06:17.246
'But 'Bandish' and 'Ek Hi Rasta'
were her favorites.'

00:06:21.016 --> 00:06:25.800
'In her old age, Daisy Irani got
attracted to films once again.'

00:06:25.880 --> 00:06:28.557
'She appeared in the film
'Shirin Farhad Ki Toh Nikal Padi'.'

00:06:28.637 --> 00:06:33.219
'I am the mad woman
whom you wanted to kill.'

00:06:34.665 --> 00:06:36.671
'Daisy Irani is the 
aunt of famous director..

00:06:36.751 --> 00:06:38.868
..Farah Khan and Sajid Khan and..'

00:06:39.098 --> 00:06:43.363
..filmmaker Zoya Akhtar and
actor director Farhan Akhtar.'

00:06:43.443 --> 00:06:46.855
'Why are you smoking a hookah?
- Why do you care?'

00:06:46.935 --> 00:06:50.322
'Daisy Irani will always
be remembered with pride..

00:06:50.402 --> 00:06:52.909
..in the history of Indian Cinema.'

